**Markdown to HTML Conversion Function**
=====================================

Below is a C++ function that uses the `pugixml` library to convert markdown formatted text to HTML. This function takes a reference to a `std::string` containing markdown text and returns a `std::string` containing the corresponding HTML text.

### Dependencies

*   `pugixml` library for parsing markdown to HTML
*   `std::string` for input and output

### Code

```cpp
#include <pugixml.hpp>
#include <string>

/**
 * Converts markdown formatted text to HTML.
 *
 * @param markdownText Reference to a string containing markdown text.
 * @return A string containing the corresponding HTML text.
 */
std::string markdownToHtml(const std::string& markdownText) {
    pugi::xml_document doc;
    pugi::xml_parse_result result = doc.load_string(markdownText.c_str());

    if (!result) {
        // Handle parsing errors
        return "Error parsing markdown text: " + std::string(result.description());
    }

    pugi::xml_node root = doc.document_element();
    std::string htmlText;
    pugi::xml_print_settings printSettings;
    printSettings.m_indent = 0;
    pugi::xml_writer_settings writerSettings;
    writerSettings.m_indent = 0;
    pugi::xml_writer writer(&htmlText, writerSettings);

    root.print(writer, printSettings);

    return htmlText;
}
```

### Usage

```cpp
int main() {
    std::string markdownText = "# Heading\n## Subheading\nThis is a paragraph.";
    std::string htmlText = markdownToHtml(markdownText);
    std::cout << htmlText << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

### Notes

